      {
        "id": 12,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 4,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Crisis",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "This beat raises the stakes to their highest level yet, bringing a low for the Protagonist(s) and their relationship. An event or betrayal occurs which breaks the bond of trust, and the Protagonist falls back into their fear or false beliefs from before as they see them manifest before them. This often leads to a breakdown of the relationship and gives the reader the impression they will never be together."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "External: What event or betrayal triggers the characters' fear about their relationship, forcing them back into their false beliefs? (e.g. one choosing their external goals over their internal, like accepting a job in another city; or one sees the other with an ex-partner; or life interferes in other ways, like a family member planting seeds of doubt.)"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Internal: How do the characters realize the relationship is over? This is often a confirmation of doubts or false beliefs. (e.g. they knew the other cannot be trusted, and this event proves it; a Protagonist lets their guard down and the other takes a job in another city; or when faced with a decision, a Protagonist chooses their external goal over their internal goal.)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Crisis should occur at around the 68% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
