              {
                "text": "Pinch Point 2 introduces another glance at the inner conflict of the Protagonists. The intimacy and relationship are continuing to grow, but inner struggles and doubts begin to resurface. These are the inner conflicts that must be resolved before the Protagonists can receive love."
