          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The tension continues to rise as another new development raises the stakes. This section sets the Protagonists on a false victory or false defeat. In a false victory, it appears as though the Protagonists will commit to each other; a false defeat will give the impression they will never find their way together."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "External: What visible sign of commitment do the Protagonists offer? (e.g. one or both could profess their love, they could surrender to the idea that it is true love, or they may have their first intimate moment.)"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Internal: How are the Protagonists doomed to fail due to internal struggles or dedication to their goals? (e.g. one Protagonist may refuse the profession of love, may recommit to their external goals, or back away due to inner conflict like feeling unworthy/unprepared for love.)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
