                "text": "Middle of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Through external forces, chance, or a life event, the Protagonists meet for the first time. Occasionally there will be an instant attraction, in which case there should be an obstacle preventing them from being together; however, typically there is instant dislike, and one or both Protagonists refuse the relationship. Readers should be able to glimpse the Protagonists could be romantically right for each other... in time."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Pick an Inciting Incident that brings the Protagonists together (e.g. a vacation, new job, family introduction, or a stressful moment like severe weather or natural disaster)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create conflict between the Protagonists (e.g. different life perspectives, different values, personality clashes, or an external obstacle like a disapproving family)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": " Demonstrate how right the Protagonists could be right for each other and why/how they are not ready."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
